<paragraph blockId="8.[813,1020,263,288]" box="[813,1020,263,288]" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">STATUS. — Resident?</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[811,1455,310,547]" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">
REMARK. — 
<emphasis box="[941,1090,311,334]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">P. c. spinetorum</emphasis>
was described by Bates from “Haute Volta, 100 Km W of Say” (
<bibRefCitation author="BOUET G." box="[1074,1190,337,361]" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" refId="ref65216" refString="BOUET G. 1955. - Faune de l'Union Francaise. XVI. Oiseaux de l'Afrique tropicale (Premiere partie). Office de la Recherche scientifique et Tecnique Outre-mer, Librairie Larose, Paris, 412 p." type="book" year="1955">Bouet 1955</bibRefCitation>
), which is nowadays in 
<collectingCountry name="Nigeria" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
. In fact, map of 
<bibRefCitation author="BORROW N. &amp; DEMEY R." box="[1019,1267,364,388]" pageId="8" pageNumber="33" refId="ref65186" refString="BORROW N. &amp; DEMEY R. 2014. - Field Guide of the Birds of Western Africa. II edition. Christopher Helm, London, 592 p." type="book" year="2014">Borrow &amp; Demey (2014)</bibRefCitation>
shows only a patch near the border between 
<collectingCountry box="[1053,1181,390,414]" name="Burkina Faso" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">Burkina Faso</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1229,1305,390,414]" name="Nigeria" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
. The specimens of the SMF bird collection (
<accessionNumber box="[1075,1195,417,441]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/SMF11390" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">SMF 11390</accessionNumber>
, 11391, 14653, 14654) are from a “fetish market”, thus the locality is uncertain and not verifiable (G. Mayr pers. comm. 2020). We found no other confirmed record, so the presence and status of this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[1326,1455,496,520]" name="Burkina Faso" pageId="8" pageNumber="33">Burkina Faso</collectingCountry>
need further assessment.
</paragraph>
